[{"id":"block_1750311486562_ex3ceuj44","type":"content","data":"C programming language, often referred to simply as C, is one of the most influential and widely used programming languages in the world. Developed in the early 1970s by Dennis Ritchie at Bell Labs, C has laid the groundwork for many other languages and remains a core skill for programmers, especially those interested in system software, embedded systems, and high-performance applications.","placeholder":"Start writing your content..."},{"id":"block_1750352064599_memvhcnkw","type":"image","data":"https://blog-app-2025.s3.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/3d706ca9f7854959b4496105264c9c45.png","placeholder":"Enter image URL..."},{"id":"block_1750311501945_x58leutvl","type":"subtitle","data":"Why C Programming?","placeholder":"Enter subtitle..."},{"id":"block_1750311527280_ab9rvsth2","type":"content","data":"C is celebrated for its efficiency, portability, and close-to-hardware capabilities. It strikes a balance between low-level manipulation of hardware and high-level programming features, making it an ideal choice for a variety of application domains.","placeholder":"Start writing your content..."},{"id":"block_1750311533624_7t3iq68ei","type":"subtitle","data":"Key Features of C Language:","placeholder":"Enter subtitle..."},{"id":"block_1750311543371_civshzlj5","type":"content","data":"* Procedural Language: Emphasizes a sequence of functions and procedures, making the code modular and manageable.
* Low-Level Access: Provides pointers, direct memory access, and hardware interface capabilities.
* Portability: Code written in C can be compiled on different platforms with minimal modification.
* Efficiency: Offers high performance, which is essential for system-level software.","placeholder":"Start writing your content..."},{"id":"block_1750311571753_bekbs7mip","type":"subtitle","data":"Basic Syntax and Structure","placeholder":"Enter subtitle..."},{"id":"block_1750311579447_mfc7tun3t","type":"content","data":"Getting started with C involves understanding its basic syntax and structure. Here is a simple "Hello, World!" program in C:

#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    printf("Hello, World!\n");
    return 0;
}","placeholder":"Start writing your content..."},{"id":"block_1750311654766_v7pe03tcr","type":"content","data":"Conclusion","placeholder":"Start writing your content..."},{"id":"block_1750311667032_ddzd04xn3","type":"content","data":"C programming remains relevant and powerful for those interested in system-level programming, performance-critical applications, or simply understanding how computers work beneath the surface. Mastering C opens doors to a solid understanding of computing fundamentals and prepares you for advanced programming challenges.","placeholder":"Start writing your content..."},{"id":"block_1750679680810_a8ch1p5y5","type":"image","data":"https://blog-app-2025.s3.eu-north-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/945fdde924004b12a74cd2b718c1c199.jpg","placeholder":"Enter image URL..."}]
